<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>West Virginia Wins 21st NCAA National Championship, Sets NCAA Championship Record</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/rifle-west-virginia-wins-21st-ncaa-national-championship-sets-ncaa-championship-record</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/rifle-west-virginia-wins-21st-ncaa-national-championship-sets-ncaa-championship-record</guid><category>Rifle</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="2026 Rifle NCAA National Champions" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" /><br /><br />COLUMBUS, Ohio – For the 21st time in program history, the West Virginia University rifle team won the NCAA Rifle National Championship after two days of competition inside the Covelli Center in Columbus on Saturday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg"><media:title>2026 Rifle NCAA National Champions</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 15:39:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>8</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58864</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia to Host NCAA Tournament First and Second Rounds</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/womens-basketball-west-virginia-to-host-ncaa-tournament-first-and-second-rounds</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/womens-basketball-west-virginia-to-host-ncaa-tournament-first-and-second-rounds</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="we're hosting 1920x1080" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University women's basketball team is set to host the First and Second Rounds of the 2026 NCAA Women's Basketball Tournament, as announced by the NCAA on Saturday afternoon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png"><media:title>we're hosting 1920x1080</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 15:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58863</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Bounce Back to Even Series Against Baylor</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/baseball-mountaineers-bounce-back-to-even-series-against-baylor</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/baseball-mountaineers-bounce-back-to-even-series-against-baylor</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tyrus Hall" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/ENX09262.jpeg" /><br /><br />WACO, Texas – The West Virginia University baseball team evened up the series with Baylor, Saturday afternoon, defeating the Bears, 13-2, in seven innings. The Mountaineers improve to 12-4 overall and 1-1 in conference play while Baylor falls to 11-7 and 1-1 in the Big 12.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/ENX09262.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/ENX09262.jpeg"><media:title>Tyrus Hall</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/ENX09262.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 19:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58867</s:story_id></item><item><title>Michael’s 8-Under-Par 64 Leads WVU on Saturday</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/golf-michaels-8-under-par-64-leads-wvu-on-saturday</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/golf-michaels-8-under-par-64-leads-wvu-on-saturday</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Nemacolin Collegiate Invitational action" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/9/30/18_GOLF_ACTION_G2x9l.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University freshman golfer Jack Michael shot an 8-under-par 64 to lead the Mountaineers to a 15-under-par round on moving day at the Schenkel Invitational in Statesboro, Georgia.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/18_GOLF_ACTION_G2x9l.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/18_GOLF_ACTION_G2x9l.jpg"><media:title>Nemacolin Collegiate Invitational action</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/18_GOLF_ACTION_G2x9l.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 18:20:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58866</s:story_id></item><item><title>Tennis Comes Up Short at No. 45 BYU</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/tennis-comes-up-short-at-no-45-byu</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/tennis-comes-up-short-at-no-45-byu</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Julie Bousseau" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/GB707914.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team (6-7, 0-7 Big 12) dropped a 4-2 decision to No. 45 BYU (13-4, 2-3 Big 12) on Saturday afternoon in Provo, Utah.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/GB707914.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/GB707914.jpg"><media:title>Julie Bousseau</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/GB707914.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 17:16:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>15</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58865</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Drop Big 12 Opener to Baylor</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/baseball-mountaineers-drop-big-12-opener-to-baylor</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/baseball-mountaineers-drop-big-12-opener-to-baylor</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Brock Wills" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" /><br /><br />WACO, Texas – The West Virginia University baseball team dropped its Big 12 opener, 7-6, Friday evening at Baylor. The Mountaineers fall to 11-4 overall while the Bears improve to 11-6.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg"><media:title>Brock Wills</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 23:22:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58862</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Scores Fourth Straight 195.0+ Score at No. 21 NC State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/gymnastics-west-virginia-scores-fourth-straight-195-0-score-at-no-21-nc-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/gymnastics-west-virginia-scores-fourth-straight-195-0-score-at-no-21-nc-state</guid><category>Gymnastics</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="sophia rice" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/13/GB703095.jpg" /><br /><br />RALEIGH, N.C. – The West Virginia University gymnastics team scored a 195.725 to finish in second place behind No. 21 NC State, who scored a 196.65, inside Valvano Arena in Raleigh, North Carolina, on Friday night.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/GB703095.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/GB703095.jpg"><media:title>sophia rice</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/GB703095.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 22:07:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>11</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58861</s:story_id></item><item><title>Naukot Finishes Seventh in 5,000 Meters at NCAA Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/track-field-naukot-finishes-seventh-in-5-000-meters-at-ncaa-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/track-field-naukot-finishes-seventh-in-5-000-meters-at-ncaa-championships</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Joy Naukot" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/5/joynaukot.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University sophomore Joy Naukot earned First Team All-America honors after finishing seventh in the women's 5,000 meters at the NCAA Indoor Track and Field Championships on Friday evening in Fayetteville, Ark.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/5/joynaukot.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/5/joynaukot.png"><media:title>Joy Naukot</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/5/joynaukot.png" length="1" typ